    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear u on the poverty trap thing, but isn't it also just a fact that some studies show the benefits are outweighed by the cost to the workforce? it feels like you're mostly focusing on the pros, but isn't it more accurate to say that these programs are a major factor in why some people opt out of the labor market entirely?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
